 <text>
  <front>
   <head>FRIENDSHIP.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">FRIENDSHIP, thou Charmer of the Mind,</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">Thou sweet deluding III,</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">The brightest Minute Mortals find,</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">And sharpest Hour we feel.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="2" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Fate has divided all our shares</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">Of Pleasure and of Pain,</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">In Love the Comforts and the Cares</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">Are mix'd and joyn'd again.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="3" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">But whilst in Floods our Sorrow rolls,</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">And Drops of Joy are few,</l>
     <l n="11" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">This dear Delight of Mingling Souls</l>
     <l n="12" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">Serves but to swell our Woe.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="4" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="13" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Oh! why should Bliss depart in haste,</l>
     <l n="14" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">And Friendship stay to moan?</l>
     <l n="15" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Why the fond Passion cling so fast,</l>
     <l n="16" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">When every Joy is gone?</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="5" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="17" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Yet never let our Hearts divide,</l>
     <l n="18" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">Not Death dissolve the Chain:</l>
     <l n="19" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">For Love and Joy were once ally'd,</l>
     <l n="20" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">And must be joyn'd again.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
  </body>
